Another questionable move by White.  White advances the h4 pawn which compromises the king side pawn structure if White intends to castle in that direction.  White might have been trying to prevent moving the knight from f3 (which is threatening to capture Black's d pawn).   however i this position, White can simple move Bf4 which still gives him an active bishop although he did allow Black to develop his BSB.
